olyn Osiek, R.S.C.J.) engaged in a research trip to Rome and Tunisia to investigate imperial period burials first hand. Commemorting the Dead is the result of a three year scholarly conversation on their findings.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aBurial. 0aFuneral rites and ceremoniesxRome. 0aFuneral rites and ceremonieszRome. 0aFuneral rites and ceremonies. 0aFuneral servicexRome (Empire)xRömisches Reich. 0aFuneral service. 0aJewish funeral rites and ceremonies. 4aBestattung. 4aChristentum /Geschichte. 4aChristliche Kunst. 7aHISTORY / Ancient / Rome.2bisacsh  aArt (Early Christian, Jewish).  aBurial.1 aBalch, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBodel, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrink, Laurie, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGreen, Deborah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGreen, Deborah, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHirschfeld, Amy K., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJensen, Robin M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMitchell, Margaret M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOsiek, Carolyn, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSaller, Richard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSaller, Richard.1 aStevens, Susan T., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWallace-Hadrill, Andrew, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1z978311023857008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA The